ccnBKXQLgyCo3Fe23umavpP7fV6SmyUsWcF_JCwb6c_X9mGf23LinD8tPONghhR4PgSW9p-8zu0=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating git issues and Android support**\\n\\nI’m wondering why git diff doesn’t show untracked files unless I use --no-index. Maybe I don’t need cat? I could try git diff --stat. There's a potential issue with the method determineAndroidSupportByAddressSize, which leads to concerns about Android32 tests given that they expect Android32, but now we have Android64. It's tricky since dropping support for Android32 might not be ideal if external workflows are affected. Should I consider implementing support for both versions and preserve coverage? Maybe dynamic access reporting could help?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Android test coverage**\\n\\nI’m noticing that the existing Android32 test calls the same path, but the Android32 class isn’t loading due to the accessor being 64. This means it shows as uncovered. While both classes exist in the source, I need to ensure high-coverage integration testing doesn’t regress. I’m considering how I can still cover Android32 while maintaining a global Memory long. Using reflection might be necessary, but relying on it can be problematic. I wonder if creating distinct test modules could be an alternative solution?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Android class access**\\n\\nI’m considering whether to use a static \\\"active class\\\" that calls the Android64MemoryAccessor constructor through a helper from com.google.protobuf. However, since private inner classes are inaccessible even within the same package, that’s a no-go. Using MethodHandles for private lookup or any dynamic calls from the test might not be possible either. I’m thinking about covering the active field by invoking the actual getStaticObject, but I still need that private class. Should I define libcore.io.Memory with long methods in the main test file instead?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_bGoyYmCIJuAFmYRCnRQg5MiF|fc_01f9d6b1d9b76f790169f2dac9a0c48196bb434667f7f0bd07", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git add tests/src/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-javalite/3.25.5/src/test/java/libcore/io/Memory.java tests/src/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-javalite/3.25.5/src/test/java/com_google_protobuf/protobuf_javalite/UnsafeUtilInnerAndroid64MemoryAccessorTest.java && git status --short"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1284, "output": 783, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31251, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777523390028, "responseId": "resp_01f9d6b1d9b76f790169f2dabe82dc8196bfdb0f944e4e8c48"}}
